Thank you Dirk Welzien (New York Life Agent in San Ramon, CA), for supporting the Walnut Creek Aquanuts Synchronized Swimming Team during the 2011-2012 season!

It has been a successful year for WCA! So far our athletes brought home 51 medals in various competitions throughout the country: 22 gold, 15 silver and 14 bronze.  We competed in solos, duets, trios and team competitions with the strongest clubs in the country. More competitions, including the Nationals, are yet to come.

WCA Alumna (Maria Koroleva) will be representing the United States in the Olympic Games in London this summer, plus thirteen WCA swimmers will be representing the Junior/Age Group national teams. 

Thank you for helping us train future Olympians. Without your help, we would not be able to provide the girls in Walnut Creek, San Ramon and surrounding communities with the training they need to reach their dreams!

Hi! Looking for agents who want to get involved with our industry here in Kansas City!                                                                                     
Whether you're new to NAIFA, or have been a member for several years, this section provides you with resources geared specifically to your career development needs as a young insurance or financial advisor. We provide you with a variety of tools that you can use to better equip yourself to overcome challenges and achieve your professional goals. Learn ideas on how to grow your business, take advantage of NAIFA's first-rate sales and skills training and receive discounts on a range of professional resources.
NAIFA created the Young Advisors Team (YAT) for members who are 40 years of age and under, or within their first five years in the industry. Purpose is to ensure that young and new advisors receive the vital tools, resources, and networks necessary to succeed in the financial services industry. 
There is no cost associated with being part of YAT; if you're 40 and under or within your first five years in the business, you are automatically part of YAT.
If you are interested friend YAT, and you will get updates and meeting times! We all have a voice, together we can leave a legacy!

My Mom is a nurse and educator. She graduated from Monmonth School of Nursing,Monmonth Hospital,Monmonth,NJ in 1940.She was President of her class.She taught nursing and labatory technology for 20+ years. She was ask by our local hospital to start a cardiac unit. She did and she also shared her knowledge with other nurses. She found out she could not retire(it just wasn't her),so she worked for a long-term care facility. Yes,shewas older than most of her patients. She was awarded the top nursing award "North Carolina's Great 100 Nurses". At the time of her award,she had the most "active years of service" - 60 years(and she was still working). Finally,at age 92 she did retire. She lives with me & she is 99 years old! Yes,I am planning her 100th Birthday Party. My mother has spent her adult life educating people in healthcare and saving and improving the lives of her patients. I have always been proud of her! She has always been my hero!
Sunday is Mother’s Day. Click here to pay tribute to your Mom – or perhaps someone who is like a mother to you.

2012 Fund Drive -- URGENT ACTION needed! 

We appeal to the generosity of those supporters who have not yet responded with a contribution. 

S.F. Crisis Care is sustained by its donors like you! It has no other substantial source of income to cover annual expenses. The generosity of those who support Survivors of Sudden Deaths like Suicide, Sudden Infant Deaths, Accidents, Traumatic Injury and Violence keeps us going. 

S.F. Crisis Care will be unable to continue its normal service if we fail to reach this year's fundraising goal. 

If you can, please support this fundraising campaign! 

If you have ever considered supporting S.F. Crisis Care, this is the moment to act. 

Please send your donation now! 

All the information you need to send a donation can be found at: http://www.crisiscare.us/sf 

Here is how you can donate: 
To make a contribution by good ol' paper check, just mail your donation to: 

S.F. Crisis Care 
P.O. Box 193046 
San Francisco, CA 94119 

To contribute online, just go to www.crisiscare.us/sf 
Hit DONATE button. There you can: 

To make regular periodic contributions from your checking account, you can set that up through your bank's free online billpay system. 

To make either a one-time or regular contributions with your credit or check card. Click there to go to our secure donations page at Network For Good.
